The paper discusses the use of unsupervised deep learning to identify patterns in physiological responses to hemodynamic stress. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as neural networks (cs.NE). The use of convolutional encoder models suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the analysis of clusters and embeddings suggests a focus on clustering and unsupervised learning (cs.CE).
